@node "Menus" "Control Panel Guide - Menus"
@{b}@{u}Pull Down Menus@{ub}@{uu}

Control Panel 6 has a series of menus, most of which also appear as buttons,
and all include a hotkey which can be used to run that option.

The options that do not appear as buttons are as follows

@{fg shine}@{b}@{u}PROJECT@{uu}@{ub}@{fg text}

About - Version and Contact Information
Help  - Brings up this documentation

Quit  - Exits Control Panel 6

@{fg shine}@{B}@{u}OPTIONS@{ub}@{uu}@{fg text}

Control Panel 6 allows configurable menu items , 3 of
which also appear as buttons on the main Control Panel.

These options can be configured by using the options editor availble through
the prefs button.

@{fg shine}@{B}@{U}USERS@{ub}@{uu}@{fg text}

Control Panel 6 allows you to have several users using your AmiTCP setup,
the details are entered using the @{"Change User" link "ChangeUser"} buttons
and this menu option allows you to quickly select any of the configured
users.

Once selected Control Panel will alter system variables to that users
details and will also change to the Home directory of that user.

@{fg shine}@{b}@{u}EDIT@{fg text}@{ub}@{UU}

The edit menu allows you to edit a designated file by selecting it from the
menu, the edit menu options being configured using the prefs/edit menu item.
(see above)

You may choose what editor you wish to use by setting the env:editor
environment variable.

e.g.

Setenv Editor sys:tools/supered

@endnode

@node "Project" "Control Panel Guide - Project Menu"
@{b}@{u}Project Menu@{uu}@{ub}

@{b}About@{ub}

Show details about Control Panel 6, including your user number and my
contact details.

@{b}Help@{ub}

Brings up this documentation

@{b}Quit@{ub}

Quits Control Panel, and saves window position is save position function is
enabled, this is the same as the End button.

@endnode

@node "logfile" "Control Panel Guide - Logfile"
@{B}@{u}Connection Log File@{ub}@{uu}

The logfile stores details about how long you have been connected to the
net, it stores this information in the same format as NComm so that
Phonebill analysing programs can be used to calculate the cost of your
calls.

The logfile can be enabled and selected by using the @{"prefs/main" link
"prefsmain"} menu item in the project menu.

@endnode
@node "statusdisplay" "Control Panel Guide - Status Display"
@{b}@{u}Status Display@{ub}@{uu}

This shows information such as the current users, user name and realname.

It also shows the current time and date, and how long you have been
connected.

The connect time will only operate when used with @{"Amiconnect" alink "Amiconnect" 0} or a modified
startnet/link script. A modified link script is included for Demon users,
other uses should add the following arexx commands to the scripts they used
to connect to the net;

Just after the command which gets your modem to dialout

Address CP6PORT "GO_CONNECTED {PopName} {Pop Phone Number}"

and just after the command which disconnect you from the net

Address CP6PORT "GO_DISCONNECTED"

This connect time will be saved to the @{"logfile" link "logfile"}.
@endnode

@node "Amiconnect" "Control Panel Guide - Amiconnect"
@{B}@{u}Amiconnect@{uu}@{ub}

This is a program which is a dialer and an Amitcp4 configuration program, it
replaces startnet,any dialler and/or link script.

This is now included an installed with CP6.
@endnode

@node "CPIS" "Control Panel Guide - Control Panel Integrated Services"
@{b}@{u}Control Panel Integrated Services@{uu}@{ub}

This is a combined frontend for some of the small utilities which
can be used with AmiTCP, these utilities being ping,askhost,traceroute and
netstat.

As each of these require slightly different parameters the display changes
according to which service is currently selected.

To use this front end select the service you require using the radio buttons
and then enter any parameters required using the relevant entry boxes and
gadgets.

------------------------------------------------------------------
|                                                                |
|Select Service                   HOST NAME                      |
|                                 @{bg shine}                            @{bg back}   |
|@{fg shine}@{"o" link ""}@{fg text} Traceroute                    TRACEROUTE TIME OUT *          |
|@{fg shine}@{"o" link ""}@{fg text} Ping                          @{bg fill}              |        @{bg back}  @{bg text}   @{bg back}   |
|@{fg shine}@{"o" link ""}@{fg text} Askhost                       NETSTAT TYPE                   |
|@{fg shine}@{"o" link ""}@{fg text} Netstat                       @{bg highlight}                            @{bg back}   |
|                                                                |
|                                                                |
|                     @{"Start" link ""}             @{"Cancel" link ""}                 |
|                                                                |
------------------------------------------------------------------

* when ping selected reads NUMBER OF PING PACKETS TO SEND instead

@{" " link ""} - Normal Button
@{fg shine}@{"o" link ""}@{fg text} - Radio Button
@{bg shine}  @{bg back} - String Entry Gadget
@{bg text}  @{bg back} - Integer Entry Gadget
@{bg fill}  @{bg back} - Slider Gadget
@{bg highlight}  @{bg back} - Cycle Gadget

@endnode

@node "preferences" "Control Panel Guide - Preferences"
@{B}@{u}Preferences@{ub}@{uu}

Preferences are now handles by the separate programs Prefs.exe and
ControlPanelPrefs. Please see the separate guidefile for more details.

@endnode


@node "Mode" "Control Panel Guide - Mini Control Panel"
@{B}@{u}Control Panel Mini Mode @{ub}@{uu}

Control Panel now has 3 display modes, these being

Standard - big display
Horizontal - Thin horizontal strip
Vertical - This vertical strip

@endnode

